orkshire, England, United Kingdom","of Ovenden, Halifax, Yorkshire, Eng.":"Ovenden, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Kempe","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Erna, Ilse.  Scandinavian Detlev, Gunhild.","English, Scottish, Dutch, and North German: variant of   Kemp  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Kemp","meanings":["English, Scottish, Dutch, and North German: status name for a champion, Middle English and Middle Low German <i>kempe</i>. In the Middle Ages a champion was a professional fighter on behalf of others; for example the King's Champion, at the coronation, had the duty of issuing a general challenge to battle to anyone who denied the king's right to the throne. The Middle English word corresponds to Old English <i>cempa</i> and Old Norse <i>kempa</i> ‘warrior’; both these go back to ancient Germanic <i>campo</i> ‘warrior’, which is the source of the Dutch and North German name, corresponding to High German   Kampf  .","Dutch and North German (North Rhine-Westphalia): from the personal name <i>Kempe</i>, <i>Kampe</i>; see 1 above.","Dutch and Flemish: metonymic occupational name for someone who grew or processed hemp, from Middle Dutch <i>canep</i> ‘hemp’."]}]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Alice Kempe was born about 1541, in Ovenden, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom. She married Richard Greenwood in 1562, in Stapleford, Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"abt 1541–":"umbes 1541–Surnud","1537–Male":"1537–Surnud","1569–Female":"1569–Surnud","1541–Female":"1541–Surnud","1569":"1569","1541":"1541","1562":"1562","17 Apr 1569":"27. aprill 1569","abt 1541":"umbes 1541","1537":"1537","Stapleford, Cambridgeshire, England":"Stapleford, Cambridgeshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Ovenden, Halifax, Yorkshire, Eng.":"Ovenden, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","of Ovenden, Halifax, Yorkshire, Eng.":"Ovenden, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"abt 1541–":"noin 1541–Kuollut","1537–Male":"1537–Kuollut","1569–Female":"1569–Kuollut","1541–Female":"1541–Kuollut","1569":"1569","1541":"1541","1562":"1562","17 Apr 1569":"27. huhtikuuta 1569","abt 1541":"noin 1541","1537":"1537","Stapleford, Cambridgeshire, England":"Stapleford, Cambridgeshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Ovenden, Halifax, Yorkshire, Eng.":"Ovenden, Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","of Ovenden, Halifax, Yorkshire, Eng.":"Ovenden, Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"abt 1541–":"environ 1541–Décédée","1537–Male":"1537–Décédé","1569–Female":"1569–Décédée","1541–Female":"1541–Décédée","1569":"1569","1541":"1541","1562":"1562","17 Apr 1569":"27 avril 1569","abt 1541":"environ 1541","1537":"1537","Stapleford, Cambridgeshire, England":"Stapleford, Cambridgeshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Ovenden, Halifax, Yorkshire, Eng.":"Ovenden, Everwyck, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","of Ovenden, Halifax, Yorkshire, Eng.":"Ovenden, Everwyck, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Alice Kempe est née environ 1541, à Ovenden, Everwyc